# ── How env files work here ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Vite loads files in this order (later overrides earlier):
#   1. frontend/.env                   — always loaded; gitignored; for local dev
#   2. frontend/.env.local             — always loaded; gitignored; per-machine
#   3. frontend/.env.production        — loaded only by `vite build`; COMMITTED
#                                        (public values only)
#   4. frontend/.env.production.local  — loaded only by `vite build`; gitignored
#                                        (secrets — PostHog key, Apple IDs, etc.)
#
# This file is a template. Copy to .env for local development.

# ── API URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave empty (or unset) for local development — Vite proxies /api calls to
# localhost:8000 automatically via vite.config.js. Production builds get the
# Railway URL automatically via the committed .env.production file.
VITE_API_URL=

# ── PostHog analytics ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a project at https://posthog.com and grab the "Project API key" from
# Settings → Project. The KEY IS A SECRET — for production builds, put it in
# .env.production.local (gitignored), NOT .env.production (committed).
#
# Leaving it unset is fine: analytics silently no-ops. Vercel reads VITE_POSTHOG_KEY
# from its own dashboard env vars for the web deploy.
# VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=phc_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# PostHog API host — only override if you use the EU instance.
# Default: https://us.i.posthog.com
# VITE_POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.i.posthog.com

# ── Sign in with Apple ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Services ID configured in the Apple Developer portal. When unset, the
# Apple sign-in button is hidden everywhere and only Google is offered.
# The backend must also have APPLE_CLIENT_ID set to the same value.
# Not a secret — fine to commit to .env.production once you have one.
# VITE_APPLE_CLIENT_ID=com.peytonhl.contour.signin
